'''Athenae''' or '''Athenai''' ({{lang-grc|Ἀθῆναι}}) was a town of [[ancient Boeotia]], on the river [[Triton River|Triton]], and near [[Lake Copais]]. Athenae, along with the neighbouring town of [[Eleusis (Boeotia)|Eleusis]], was destroyed by an inundation.<ref>{{Cite Strabo|ix. p.407}}</ref><ref>{{Cite Pausanias|9|24|2}}</ref>
