The '''Fox Hollow Festival''' or '''Fox Hollow Festival of Traditional Music and Arts''' was a [[folk festival]] held on the estate of folksingers [[Beers Family|Bob and Evelyne Beers]] <ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=65R0tN7cgs0C&pg=PA75&lpg=PA75&dq=%22Fox+Hollow+folk+Festival%22&source=bl&ots=oA6BVj34ov&sig=xlZj08nmfadrEt7ihJ54HAc1btw&hl=en&ei=jmuJSoPALZbKtgen89nnDA&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=3#v=onepage&q=%22Fox%20Hollow%20folk%20Festival%22&f=false''A History of Folk Music Festivals in the United States: Feasts of Musical Celebration – Issue 11 of American Folk Music and Musicians Series, No. 11''] [[Ronald D. Cohen]], [[Rowman & Littlefield]], 2008 {{ISBN|0-8108-6202-6}}</ref> in [[Petersburgh, New York]] each summer from 1966 to 1980,<ref>[http://www.wshu.org/profiles/2004/pr040618.php ''Folk Festivals, Part 2: The Fox Hollow-Old Songs Connection'']</ref> usually in August.
